1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,360
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,360 --> 00:00:04,360
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,360 --> 00:00:07,320
My name is Kathryn and we're going to the gym today, right Marco?
我是Kathryn，我们今天要去健身房，对吧，Marco？

4
00:00:07,320 --> 00:00:08,320
That's right.
没错。

5
00:00:08,320 --> 00:00:14,240
Today we're going to go to the gym and we're going to try to lose weight or to get in shape.
今天我们要去健身房，尝试减肥或者塑形。

6
00:00:14,240 --> 00:00:19,180
So before we start out though, there is a phrasal verb that we should take a look at.
不过在我们开始之前，有一个短语动词需要先看一下。

7
00:00:19,180 --> 00:00:24,640
So today in Vocabulary Preview, we're looking at this phrase, to work out or working out.
所以在今天的词汇预览中，我们要看这个短语：to work out 或 working out。

8
00:00:24,640 --> 00:00:25,640
That's right.
没错。

9
00:00:25,640 --> 00:00:27,160
So when we go to the gym, this is what we do.
所以当我们去健身房时，这就是我们要做的事情。

10
00:00:27,160 --> 00:00:33,280
We go there to work out, to exercise or to tone up.
我们去那里锻炼、运动或者塑形。

11
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:39,140
This is just a way of saying that I'm going to go somewhere like a gym to exercise myself.
这只是说我要去健身房之类的地方锻炼身体的一种方式。

12
00:00:39,140 --> 00:00:40,140
That's right.
没错。

13
00:00:40,140 --> 00:00:43,860
So with that in mind, we're going to go to the gym, we're going to work out and we're
所以带着这个想法，我们要去健身房，我们要锻炼，而且我们

14
00:00:43,860 --> 00:00:54,040
going to learn a lot of words today about what exactly goes on in the gym.
今天会学到很多关于健身房具体活动的词汇。

15
00:00:54,040 --> 00:00:55,640
Do you want to go catch a movie tonight?
今晚想去看电影吗？

16
00:00:55,640 --> 00:00:56,640
I can't.
不行。

17
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:57,640
I have to go to the gym.
我得去健身房。

18
00:00:57,640 --> 00:00:58,640
Come on.
别这样嘛。

19
00:00:58,640 --> 00:00:59,640
You can go tomorrow.
你可以明天去。

20
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:00,640
Just skip it today.
今天就跳过吧。

21
00:01:00,640 --> 00:01:01,640
It's not as if you're going to get in trouble.
又不是说你会惹上麻烦。

22
00:01:01,640 --> 00:01:03,160
Actually, I will.
其实，我会的。

23
00:01:03,160 --> 00:01:06,400
I'm working out with a personal trainer that gets on my case if I don't go.
我正在跟一个私人教练锻炼，如果我不去，他就会催我。

24
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:10,400
I like it because it makes me feel more obligated to go and get healthy.
我喜欢这样，因为它让我更有义务去锻炼，变得更健康。

25
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:11,400
That's cool.
那挺酷的。

26
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:13,640
Does your personal trainer basically teach you how to work out?
你的私人教练基本上是教你如何锻炼吗？

27
00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:14,640
Yeah.
是的。

28
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:18,520
He makes a workout plan depending on the areas I want to work on or the muscles I want to
他会根据我想锻炼的部位或想练的肌肉制定一个锻炼计划，

29
00:01:18,520 --> 00:01:19,520
build.
比如，为了让我腹肌、胸肌和二头肌的线条更好，他让我用自由重量训练。

30
00:01:19,520 --> 00:01:23,840
Like for example, in order to get better muscle tone in my abs, pecs and biceps, he makes
然后对于我的股四头肌、小腿和腘绳肌，我会做抬腿或深蹲。

31
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:25,240
me work out with free weights.
听起来你确实在塑形了。

32
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:28,960
Then for my quads, calves and hamstrings, I do leg lifts or squats.
好的。

33
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:31,480
Sounds like you're really getting into shape.
那么，现在我们回来了。

34
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:33,520
All right.
让我们来看看“语言要点”部分。

35
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:35,720
So, now we're back.
“语言要点”。

36
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:40,400
Let's take a look at Language Takeaway.
好的。

37
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:41,400
Language Takeaway.
首先，在今天的对话中，我们听到了很多关于一个叫私人教练的人。

38
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:43,400
All right.
私人教练。

39
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:47,440
First of all, in today's dialogue, we heard a lot about this person called a personal
首先，在今天的对话中，我们听到了很多关于一个叫私人教练的人。

40
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:48,440
trainer.
私人教练。

41
00:01:48,440 --> 00:01:50,400
What does a personal trainer do, Marco?
私人教练是做什么的，马可？

42
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:56,000
So basically, you have a person that is your coach, the person that guides you and teaches
基本上，就是有一个人当你的教练，指导你、教你

43
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:59,680
you how to work out or what you should do.
如何锻炼或者该做什么。

44
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:00,680
All right.
好的。

45
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:02,360
So, personal means it's just for me.
所以，“私人”意味着只为我服务。

46
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:04,080
This person is only helping me.
这个人只帮助我一个人。

47
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:08,840
A trainer is someone who, like you say, gives me guidance.
教练就是像你说的那样，给我指导的人。

48
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:13,960
So personal trainer is someone who will work with me every day or maybe one time a week
所以私人教练就是每天或每周一次和我一起工作的人，

49
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:17,200
to really get the most out of my workout.
让我的锻炼效果最大化。

50
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:18,200
That's right.
没错。

51
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:20,160
So that is a personal trainer.
这就是私人教练。

52
00:02:20,160 --> 00:02:24,080
And as we said, he's going to help us to build muscle.
就像我们说的，他会帮助我们增肌。

53
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:25,800
We want to build muscle when we go to the gym.
我们去健身房就是想增肌。

54
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:26,800
All right.
好的。

55
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:31,000
So, this is an interesting one because the verb is not to grow or to make.
这个说法挺有意思，因为动词不是“生长”或“制造”。

56
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,120
The verb is to build.
动词是“建造”。

57
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:36,680
So, I have muscles, but I want my muscles to get bigger.
所以，我有肌肉，但我想让肌肉变大。

58
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:39,840
So I go to build muscles at the gym.
所以我去健身房增肌。

59
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:42,880
You might even hear this phrase, a bodybuilder.
你甚至可能听过这个词：健美运动员。

60
00:02:42,880 --> 00:02:44,720
So this idea that you make them.
就是这种“制造”肌肉的概念。

61
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:45,760
Yeah, exactly.
对，没错。

62
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:47,960
So you don't get muscle.
所以你不会得到肌肉。

63
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,380
You don't create muscle.
你不会创造肌肉。

64
00:02:49,380 --> 00:02:51,040
You build muscle.
你是锻炼肌肉。

65
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:55,800
And alongside with muscles, not only do you get them big, but you also get muscle tone.
而且除了让肌肉变大，你还能获得肌肉线条。

66
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,800
All right.
好的。

67
00:02:56,800 --> 00:03:00,620
So muscle tone basically means definition.
所以肌肉线条基本上就是指轮廓清晰。

68
00:03:00,620 --> 00:03:06,200
So maybe before you start to work out, your body is very soft.
也许在你开始锻炼之前，你的身体很软。

69
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:07,440
You can't see the muscles.
你看不到肌肉。

70
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:11,000
Well, when you start to see those muscles, you see the lines in your body.
嗯，当你开始看到那些肌肉时，你会看到身体上的线条。

71
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,320
Your skin gets tighter, not so soft.
你的皮肤变得更紧致，不那么软了。

72
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:14,840
That's called muscle tone.
这就叫肌肉线条。

73
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:15,840
That's right.
没错。

74
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:17,160
So then you can see the muscles.
所以那时你就能看到肌肉了。

75
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:18,400
That's muscle tone.
那就是肌肉线条。

76
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:21,920
And now the muscles that we most commonly go to the gym to work out, we're going to
现在，我们最常去健身房锻炼的肌肉，我们快速

77
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:24,440
name really quickly and we're going to see where they are.
说一下它们的名字，看看它们在哪里。

78
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:26,840
So the first one that we mentioned were abs.
第一个我们提到的是腹肌。

79
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:27,840
Okay.
好的。

80
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:30,400
This is an important one, especially if you want to go to the beach.
这个很重要，尤其是如果你想去海滩的话。

81
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:33,960
The abs are located on your stomach.
腹肌位于你的腹部。

82
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:38,920
So you see those kind of rectangles, those squares on your stomach.
所以你会看到腹部那些像矩形、方块一样的东西。

83
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:39,920
Those are the abs.
那些就是腹肌。

84
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:40,920
That's right.
没错。

85
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:45,680
And now for guys also, we want to work out our pecs or our pectoral muscles.
对于男性来说，我们也想锻炼胸肌或胸大肌。

86
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:51,440
So those are on your chest, below your neck, but above your stomach.
所以这些位于你的胸部，脖子下方，但腹部上方。

87
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:52,440
That's right.
没错。

88
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:55,440
And another important one on your arm, we have our biceps.
另一个重要的部位在手臂上，我们有肱二头肌。

89
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:56,440
All right.
好的。

90
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:59,880
Men usually like to show these off, or at least boys do.
男性通常喜欢炫耀这些，至少男孩们是这样。

91
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:01,160
These are on your arms.
这些在你的手臂上。

92
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:05,760
So you know when you make that L shape with your arm and you squeeze like Popeye?
你知道当你把手臂弯成L形，像大力水手那样用力时吗？

93
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:07,320
Those are your biceps.
那些就是你的肱二头肌。

94
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:08,320
Those are your biceps.
那些就是你的肱二头肌。

95
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:09,320
Exactly.
完全正确。

96
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:14,760
And now, obviously going down towards our legs now, we have our quad muscles, our quads.
现在，显然往下到我们的腿部，我们有股四头肌。

97
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:15,760
All right.
好的。

98
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:18,120
So those are on the top part of your legs, right Marco?
所以这些位于你腿部的上半部分，对吧，Marco？

99
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:19,120
In front.
在前面。

100
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,120
In front.
在前面。

101
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:21,560
So like on the top of your thigh.
就像在你大腿顶部的位置。

102
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:22,560
Exactly.
没错。

103
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:29,440
And now right behind the back part of your leg, you have your hamstrings.
现在，在你腿的后部，就是你的腘绳肌。

104
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:31,400
Hamstring.
腘绳肌。

105
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:35,520
Now you hear about this one a lot because people injure their hamstrings pretty easily
你经常听到这个词，因为人们在踢足球或跑步时很容易拉伤腘绳肌。

106
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:37,520
in football or in running.
在踢足球或跑步的时候。

107
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:38,520
Yeah, that's right.
是的，没错。

108
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:42,800
Sometimes if you're running and you didn't stretch, your muscles are not warm, you can
有时候如果你跑步前没拉伸，肌肉还没热身，你可能会

109
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:43,800
pull a hamstring.
拉伤腘绳肌。

110
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:44,800
All right.
好的。

111
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,040
So that hamstring is an important one.
所以腘绳肌很重要。

112
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:47,040
We have one more.
我们还有一个。

113
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:48,040
That's right.
没错。

114
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:51,080
We have our calves and these are in the bottom, right above our feet.
我们还有小腿，它们在腿的底部，就在脚的上方。

115
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:54,680
So I don't have any muscles except for this one because I ride my bike.
我除了这块肌肉（因为骑自行车）之外，其他肌肉都不发达。

116
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:56,240
And when you ride your bike, this gets big.
当你骑自行车时，这块肌肉会变大。

117
00:04:56,240 --> 00:05:01,920
So your calves are that part of your leg above your foot, but below your knee in the back.
所以小腿就是你脚上方、膝盖后方的那部分腿。

118
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:02,920
That's right.
没错。

119
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:03,920
The back part.
后部。

120
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:04,920
Very good.
很好。

121
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:08,720
So all of these muscles, some of the most common ones that we work out.
所以所有这些肌肉，都是我们最常锻炼的一些部位。

122
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:19,560
So now let's move on to some important phrases on Fluency Builder.
现在让我们进入流利度提升部分，学习一些重要短语。

123
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:21,120
Do you want to go catch a movie tonight?
今晚想去看场电影吗？

124
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:22,120
I can't.
我去不了。

125
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:23,120
I have to go to the gym.
我得去健身房。

126
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,120
Come on.
别这样嘛。

127
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,120
You can go tomorrow.
你可以明天去啊。

128
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:26,120
Just skip it today.
今天就跳过吧。

129
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:27,120
It's not as if you're going to get in trouble.
又不是说你会惹上什么麻烦。

130
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:28,600
Actually, I will.
其实，我会的。

131
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:31,880
I'm working out with a personal trainer that gets on my case if I don't go.
我和一个私人教练一起锻炼，如果我不去，他就会唠叨我。

132
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:35,880
I like it because it makes me feel more obligated to go and get healthy.
我喜欢这样，因为这让我更有义务去锻炼，保持健康。

133
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:36,880
That's cool.
那挺酷的。

134
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:39,120
Does your personal trainer basically teach you how to work out?
你的私人教练主要是教你如何锻炼吗？

135
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:40,120
Yeah.
是的。

136
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:44,040
He makes a workout plan depending on the areas I want to work on or the muscles I want to
他会根据我想锻炼的部位或想练的肌肉制定一个锻炼计划，

137
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:45,040
build.
比如增肌。

138
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:49,120
Like, for example, in order to get better muscle tone in my abs, pecs, and biceps, he
比如，为了让我腹肌、胸肌和二头肌线条更好，他

139
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:50,720
makes me work out with free weights.
让我用自由重量器械锻炼。

140
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:54,440
Then for my quads, calves, and hamstrings, I do leg lifts or squats.
然后对于我的股四头肌、小腿肌和腘绳肌，我会做抬腿或深蹲。

141
00:05:54,440 --> 00:06:00,360
Sounds like you're really getting into shape.
听起来你身材真的变好了。

142
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:03,820
So the beginning of the dialogue, the friends were trying to decide what to do.
所以对话开头，朋友们在商量要做什么。

143
00:06:03,820 --> 00:06:07,280
And one friend said, do you want to go catch a movie?
然后一个朋友说，你想去看场电影吗？

144
00:06:07,280 --> 00:06:08,280
That's right.
没错。

145
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:09,440
So to catch a movie.
所以是“catch a movie”。

146
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:10,800
Do you want to go catch a movie?
你想去看场电影吗？

147
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:15,320
It sounds funny because catch means to hold something in your hands after someone throws
听起来有点好笑，因为“catch”本意是别人扔过来后用手接住，

148
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:16,320
it.
接住。

149
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:17,320
So throw and catch.
所以是“扔”和“接”。

150
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:21,720
But here, it doesn't mean to actually hold something in your hands.
但在这里，它并不是真的指用手接住什么东西。

151
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:25,400
It means do you want to go see a movie?
它的意思是“你想去看电影吗？”

152
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:26,400
Right.
对。

153
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:27,400
Exactly.
完全正确。

154
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:30,360
So it's a very informal, colloquial way of saying, hey, do you want to go to the movies?
所以这是一种非常非正式、口语化的说法，意思是“嘿，你想去看电影吗？”

155
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:32,220
Do you want to go see a movie?
你想去看电影吗？

156
00:06:32,220 --> 00:06:35,000
Maybe not like a serious date or something, just for fun.
可能不是那种正式的约会之类的，只是图个乐子。

157
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,600
Do you want to go catch a movie?
你想去看场电影吗？

158
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:37,600
That's right.
没错。

159
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:38,600
Let's go catch a movie.
我们去看场电影吧。

160
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,600
All right.
好的。

161
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:41,960
So obviously we can't go to the movies because we got to go to the gym.
所以很明显我们不能去看电影，因为得去健身房。

162
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:47,280
And we have to go to the gym because our personal trainer will get on our case.
而且我们必须去健身房，因为我们的私人教练会找我们麻烦。

163
00:06:47,280 --> 00:06:50,520
